Imported module taps emitted as runtime code instead of compile-time transforms

The tap transform works correctly for user code (test 507 passes), but when taps
are defined in an imported library (profiler.kz), the tap flows are emitted as
runtime calls instead of being processed as compile-time transforms.

Symptom: Generated code contains invalid Zig like:
  koru_std.profiler.tap_event.handler(.{ .koru:start -> * = koru:start -> * });

Root cause: Transform runner or emitter not handling tap flows in imported modules.

See working test: 360_TAPS_OBSERVERS/507_meta_event_taps
